In Table (ref), each mechanism is evaluated on the candidate list generated using prompt templates shown in max-F1 column in Table (ref). However, by choosing a different set of prompts, a higher overall F1 score of 51.3% with a lower 59.9% max-F1 can be achieved by using the prob-{{arxiv_2307_03122_FO0023||FO}} method. Table (ref) in Appendix gives more details. 
This change in F1 scores shows the hardness of designing robust prompts.